@IsabellaGhement @bolkerb So the limits will default to the boundaries to the left of min(x) and right of max(x).

I think these equations work to figure it out if you need to match limits across plots of subsets of the data:

c(
  min(x) - (min(x) %% binwidth),
  max(x) + (-max(x) %% binwidth)
)

